06220nam a22004935i 9788367405119DE-B159720221205051307.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221205t20222022pl     fo  d z      eng d  a9788367405119  a(DE-B1597)637681  a(OCoLC)1347247576  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aplcPL 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04aThe mindsponge and BMF analytics for innovative thinking in social sciences and humanities. 1aWarsaw ;aBerlin : bSciendo, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (430 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tA preamble about doing research that sells -- tAcknowledgment -- tTable of contents -- tAbout the Editors and Contributors -- tList of Figures -- tList of Tables -- tChap 1: Mindsponge mechanism: Emergence, application, and potential -- tChapter 2 Mindsponge mechanism: an information processing conceptual framework -- tChapter 3: How to explore the suicidal mind: a mindsponge-based conceptualization -- tChapter 4: Trust in mindsponge: a new perspective on information reliability -- tChapter 5: Bayesian Mindsponge Framework analytics: a novel methodological approach for social sciences and humanities -- tChapter 6: Preparations for working with the Bayesian Mindsponge Framework analytics effectively -- tChapter 7: The first BMF investigation: suicidal ideation mechanism -- tChapter 8: The second BMF investigation: mindset, motivation, and book reading interest -- tChapter 9: The third BMF investigation: Internet healthcare information, trust, and personal assessment -- tChapter 10: Updated protocol for performing BMF analytics using bayesvl -- tChapter 11: Mindsponge-based theoretical reasoning on the political psychology that begets and empowers a dictator -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAcademia is a competitive environment. Early Career Researchers (ECRs) are limited in experience and resources and especially need achievements to secure and expand their careers. To help with these issues, this book offers a new approach for conducting research using the combination of mindsponge innovative thinking and Bayesian analytics. This is not just another analytics book. 1. A new perspective on psychological processes: Mindsponge is a novel approach for examining the human mind’s information processing mechanism. This conceptual framework is used to construct models in studies. The framework is highly flexible and widely applicable for many different types of information processes. The mindsponge approach can help researchers discover interesting ideas or even formulate their very own theories when investigating psychosocial phenomena. This approach brings a fresh wind to the current landscape of social sciences and humanities (SSH). 2. Easy-to-follow analysis protocol: The Bayesian Mindsponge Framework (BMF analytics) is useful in terms of computing and visualizing power but also easy to learn and apply. Contrary to being intimidating, the Bayesian analytics section of this book is presented in a reader-friendly manner with a detailed yet clear step-by-step procedure. Examples are from published BMF articles, allowing readers to immediately practice the method and quickly create their own applications. With educational purposes in mind, the book is very suitable for ECRs who are looking to innovate their research methods. 3. Advocating for low-cost, high-quality research: Doing science can be very costly. Mindsponge innovative thinking and BMF analytics help produce impactful studies using openly available data on online repositories. This is based on the authors’ previous works and experiences. The book presents examples of employing the open R package bayesvl on secondary data from different sources. With less financial constraints, researchers can have more freedom of thought to pursue their curiosity and creativity. ECRs in low- and middle-income countries may find this aspect crucial in their careers. 4. Support and collaboration: The authors share their insights from experiences in the academic publishing system to help readers get through the processes of manuscript writing and peer-reviewing more easily. The authors are also ready to support other researchers with further inquiries and collaboration opportunities at the following website, https://mindsponge.info. This book is for: a) ECRs whose only abundant resources are their innovation capacity and strength of will; b) Researchers in SSH who want to explore a novel approach to thinking and study conducting; c) Low- and middle-income countries’ researchers looking for a cost-effective research protocol; and, d) Innovative thinkers who want to turn their interesting thoughts into good publications.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aHo, Manh-Tung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLa, Viet-Phuong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLe, Tam-Tri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNguyen, Minh-Hoang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVuong, Quan-Hoang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVuong, Thu-Trang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0 cprintz978836740510240uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9788367405119423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9788367405119/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles